caption: The best!
Awesome meals! Love their salads!
Butternut quesadillas are amazing, along with their ginger lemonade.

username: It's All About The Music Joanna and Jeff

caption: Absolutely to die for!! Everything was delicious.  Wish we live closer, we'd be here every week!!

I ordered the vegan mac and cheese with broccoli... I was disappointed in how my order came out. The meal did not look appetizing and the broccoli was burned. The taste was not too bad but overall I expected better based on someone's recommendation.
Excellent food - flavorful, colorful, and easy-to-use online ordering/pickup in COVID times. Will definitely be coming back here!

One of the best nachos I’ve ever had!! Vegan cheese at it’s best!! The Margherita pizza was so delicious you can taste that the ingredients were fresh!! The sweet chili glazed tofu doesn’t disappoint, perfectly seasoned & cooked!! Staff were also nice & accomodating. Will definitely go back & recommend this place.

Went to the Garden Grille and it was really good.  They are under a reservation only policy because of the Covid.  Upon arriving the staff was friendly and we were shown to the outdoor seating.  Honestly I only gave 4 stars because the only part of the experience I didn't like was the set up of the outdoor seating.  I'm sure it will be better once they go back to indoor seating.  The food, however, was excellent. I would recommend the Nachos, and the Pizza.  Both really good, large portions, and fresh tasting.  I really loved that they offer local Yacht Club Soda.  It's always great to see business supporting other local businesses.  Great experience!  Highly Recommended.
Love the food

Poor Service. I came here and ordered the butternut squash quesadilla & it made me extremely sick - felt like I got FOOD POISONING. We also ordered the vegan Mac & Cheese and were dissatisfied by the non-flavorful taste and uncomfortable by the amount of cheese in this. I had high expectations for this place, but when you have expectations - you always get disappointed.
Best vegan friendly place around. Try the Reuben with vegan cheese and the chipotle seitan
Garden grille is probably my favorite local restaurant. They constantly rotate their menu, so there's always something new to try. They are very accommodating, and the servers are very attentive.

I really enjoyed Garden Grille, and made sure to return again the second time I visited Rhode Island as well. Delicious and fresh Vegan / Vegetarian menu and large portions.  I loved the Reggie's Raw Heaven salad! Hope to have the chance to go back sometime soon :-)
I love the food there! The service is great too! We will always come back

I can’t say I’ve had a bad anything at garden grille - meals are excellent, drinks are so good I crave them, desserts are delicious and staff is amazing! I love their classic margarita, nachos and butternut squash quesadilla. I’ve had many favorites but their menu changes often so at some point I say goodbye to a favorite dish and Discover a new one. The ones I mention above are staples, I haven’t seen them change in years. Cheers!
Best vegan food in RI.
That butternut squash quesadilla has no right to be that tasty! Definitely coming back!

Phenomenal kosher food! and relatively low prices for vegan/kosher food. We tried 8 different menu items, and absolutely loved everything we got. What a treat. Me and my friends now want to visit Providence more often - there are better food options than Boston apparently. Who knew...
Nice menu. Food was good. Small place.

Not a vegetarian/vegan but used a gift card our family member gave us for Christmas and was so happy we did. It was so delicious. We got the buffalo cauliflower bites, margarita pizza, nachos and peanut butter brownie. Everything was surprisingly so delicious. All that food for only $44. The staff on the phone and the hand off (during pandemic) were super friendly. Will 100% be coming back again.
Good food

Fantastic vegetarian place with quick and friendly service. Nothing too fancy on the menu, it’s a pretty low brow place, but the food is great and prices are fair. They’re currently only open for takeout, but they do have to go options for drinks. Great place to eat whether or not you’re a vegetarian!
Fantastic food, excellent service! Always stop by for lunch when I’m in the area.
Love this spot, I’m not a vegetarian but it’s a great place that I enjoy with my friends and family regardless since they accommodate everything and it all tastes great. The drinks are a must too!
Always delicious. Consistently good drink menu. Korean tacos are addictive.
Awesome nachos and vegan food
(Translated by Google) Shock full o 'veggies!  (Original) Chock full o' veggies!

Amazing restaurant  with a wide menu selection. Parking is very convenient and the atmosphere is down to earth and cozy. Love coming here and then grabbing a sweet treat at Wild Flour next door after.
Delicious and not "just" for healthy food

Great for vegans, vegetarians, celiacs, the health conscious or just people looking for fresh tasty food. Lemonade is refreshing and freshly made. Vegan nachos and sweet potato wedges are my faves here. Everything is made fresh to order. Great healthy delicious food!!!
Delicious, great service, and always welcome to see more veggie/vegan options!

So I am a local that eats here just about every week and I have never had an issue. I would still go back considering Saturday night was the worst service  I ever received from them. The food is good, the staff are friendly but I don't know if it was a new guy but he was horrible. What makes it even bad is we had a party of 6 and out of that 6, 3 ppl that never been to the place, so I excited for them to try the place out. I was just very disappointed with the service that night. We sat down at our table we were missing 3 forks not a big deal we got our starter fairly quickly and we put our entree orders in. I ordered the night speical which I was very excited to try. Everyone's food came out and my was last to come out again not a big deal EXCEPT it was not what I ordered. I told the server and he said they ran out of the speical. So he took my plate away and I was waiting for a menu thinking I'll just order something else, never got one I have to ask the bartender for one. I was about to order something else when our waiter came back and said they're gonna make it for you...THAT should have been my clue just to say no thanks and order the Mac and cheese but at this point he didn't give me a choice so I said whatever. I still wasn't upset just hungry. I waited for my food maybe five minutes or so when it came out it was so sloppy looking like they literally just threw it together. There was so much water on the plate the food was swimming in it. It just looked disgusting I had maybe two bits and wasn't really hungry after all if this. At this point I just wanted to leave go to wildfour to get real decent food. Our bill came and he only took part of it off the bill my boyfriend paid so he wouldn't let me see it because he knew I would make a big deal out of it which I feel is only right because with that food and how it was presented and how long I had to wait it should have been taken off the bill completely. The waiter had no communication we had to ask for a drink 3 times because he forgot and finally ask the bartender that was walking around helping ppl. Again maybe he was new or didn't know how to handle a big party but i don't know if I'll bring a big party to garden grille again. I think you guys are just good for the two of us on our regular nights. So with that being said I do like garden grille and plan to go back but I hope this will be a lesson to them to have better communication between their waiters and customers. I know ppl get busy and it wasn't that busy there like I know it can be but communication goes a long with when you're handling customers.

Came here after a terrible experience at a nearby establishment that had food reviews for vegan. Never had anything to eat there. That’s another story/review. But this place is great. Nice cozy place. Very friendly staff. Greeted at the door. Attentive staff. Food is amazing. I had the cauliflower and Risotto appetizer. Amazing flavors. For dinner I algas the Mushroom Pad Thai. Large portion great taste. Would never know what I ate was vegan. Busy too with people picking up take out orders. Will make this a regular stop when in town for business.

One of my favorite restaurants, up there with the grange. If you love leafy greens I highly suggest the sautéed greens of the day. The really understand what goes into cooking every veg dish properly. Never had a bad experience. Perfect place to get a novice veg eater acclimated to high level veg food, or just a nice date night out.
Great food !
Always awesome service and food. One of the best spots around
Great food, great waiters, great experience.
This was just what I was looking for: nice people, food, and environs! I’ll come back...for...sure.

A nice cozy little place. I had the Nachos and my wife had the mushroom pad Thai. The Nachos were tasty and it was a very large serving. I tried a bit of the pad Thai as well and thought it was tasty. Overall a good place with tasty food.

I loved this place when I was a vegetarian and still love it now that I'm a vegan! Everything is fresh and delicious, and every time an omnivore accompanies me, they're enthusiastic!  I'd love to give five stars, but there's one thing I don't like: the prices of some of the dishes. In my opinion, some dishes on the menu - for example, I had a vegan tempeh pizza that was 16 dollars! - are too expensive for a casual dining restaurant. The owner should lower some of the prices a bit or increase the portion sizes.
Try the vegan ruben.
Everything was delicious. Food and drinks
Good veggie based meals.
Delicious

I love a restaurant where I don’t have to check the ingredients to see if it has beef/pork. Fun and delicious menu. Would add a 5th star if our server was more attentive, and if our table didn’t have a film of...something...
Best vegan ever!!!

Awesome. The ambiance is good, the food is outstanding. Was introduced to this place by two carnivores who love coming here. It was amazing to find a menu where we could eat anything. And the food was outstanding. I had the eggplant parm, which is probably the best Ive ever had. Husband had the falafel, and loved it. Carnivore #1 had the portobello sandwich and raved about it. Carnivore #2 had the bean burrito for the 3rd time in a row. Cant get more of a commendation for that. She talked about the burrito the entire way there and back. The table shared the lentil chili for an app. Delicious. The service was attentive, the close tables allowed us to meet other diners and start conversations...a fantastic evening!
Great place to eat.  The music was very loud.  Food was delicious.   Wish it was a larger restaurant...

I'm a huge carnivore but Garden Grille makes me forget there's no meat in my meal lol Very tasty options on their menu. My favorite dishes are: the butternut squash quesadilla, the Ruben sandwich (taste like meat but isn't) and the cauliflower appetizer.

So wonderful as a vegetarian out for dinner with friends to look at a menu and think "You can eat anything from this menu"! The soup of the day - Lentil Chili - is simply amazing. Offered as a side, could be a meal on it's own (maybe with some vegan cheese on top). Will visit often.

Woahwoahwoah the seitan reuben is the most realistic imitation meat I have ever had. Meat eaters and veggies alike will love what this place has to offer. Not the cheapest spot but you get it back in quality and the portions are good. Service is also consistently good.
Extremely snobby waitstaff. Never going back. Very unwelcoming and unkind.
Food is okay but could be better, and bartender should not call customer "HAY" in a loud voice.

Wonderful new menu and whether you are Vegetarian or a meat eater (but no meat here), the dishes are just eclectic and superbly done for the taste buds.  The pad thai & brussel sprouts dinner was awesome.  Cool drinks too.  A must stop for great food fare!
If you're looking for delicious vegan/vegetarian grub this spot is a must.
Everything was delicious. Would highly recommend a visit!!!
Delicious food...love the Rubin
Great food and service!
Wasn't at Garden Grille.Went to Moonstar Chinese.Food very good, fresh, best quality I had in awhile.9 out 10stars.

Best roasted butternut squash quesadillas!
Great food and great service!!! I'm not even a vegetarian and I loved the food.  If you havnt tried it yet your truly missing out!!!
Fav vegan local
Wonderful atmosphere, small but space is well used, delicious food, fun specials, and pleasant wait staff.
I enjoy the vegan BLT. It's awesome. But please, bring back the chick pea korma!! The staff is very pleasant. This is a great place to go for a nice vegetarian dish.
Great place for a carnivore to learn a gentler path. Loved the food and flavors. Must try!! Who knew, you could make a delicious RUBEN without meat??
Amazing veg/vegan restaurant. Super creative entrees with local ingredients, the vegan nachos were incredible and the ratatouille pizza had an amazing crisp crust and was so satisfying.
I loved this place very well. It is simple vegan and vegetarian. Very reasonable price.
Butternut Squash Quesadilla = Amazingly Delicious! Fun vegetarian & vegan friendly cool staff! Been coming for 10+ years & I've never been disappointed!
I have never had a bad meal from Garden Grill. The spicy margarita excellent and the Seitian Reuben fabulous. 👍👍

Such a delightful surprise! So many delicious, healthy, creative menu options to choose from and a friendly and helpful staff! Loved the cauliflower tacos, ratatouille gluten-free pizza and mushroom pad thai special. Wish we had room for more!
Always delicious! You CANNOT go wrong here!
This place is a mess. Rude waiters. Never go here
The vegan version of the nachos with sour cream and cheese is so on point you will wonder if they are really vegsn
My favorite place!
Very nice spot!
Kosher vegitarian foods. $$

We've been to this Restaurant several times , and it is a Hit or Miss. Sometimes the food is good and tonight it was awful , and we should have sent it back, but due to the long wait we were hungry so we ate it anyway. People came in after us were served there meals before us.

Their extensive menu and nightly specials will please both vegetarians and vegans. The portions are generous and the flavors are tantalizing. I highly recommend the seitan appetizer with the wasabi dipping sauce that provides an invigorating kick! Service was attentive and the kitchen had our food out fast.
Consistently great
Amazing food and great service! Highly recommend.
Fantastic food and great staff.
Engaged, knowledgeable, accommodating, and friendly staff! Excellent food! Fresh ingredients! What's not to love?!?!? And, as if that wasn't enough, what a FANTASTIC soundtrack!!!  😀
Love this place. Food is so good. And menu changes depending the season. Lots of vegan options
Excellent food, try the butternut squash quesadilla!
Fresh and delicious food all the time!

If I went fully vegetarian/vegan I could see myself eating here everyday. Then again, I could see myself eating here everyday and feel like I'm not missing anything in my diet. Delicious options and plenty of vegan choices. It can be busy at peak hours but it's worth the wait. You can also get a complimentary coffee next door while you wait for a table.
Amazing food!
Oh my the Seitan Rueben is insanely good. As a New York pastrami eating Jew that says a lot!
Love it. Nachos are the bomb.
Nice food
This used to be a 5 star restaurant;then they changed the menu.
I am a vegetarian for 27 years , so this is a place for me . Many options, clean, cool ,funky , fun , healthy b, fresh quality 😁😀🙆

This place is a must for vegans and vegetarians! I go here every time I visit Rhode Island. Most of the fruits and veggies come from local farms. The dishes are always full of flavor. It is usually busy, so get there early.
Always delicious
Outstanding lunch great service..Garden Grille is my new favorite restaurant.  Go!

Wonderful dinner.  Any vegetarian/vegan who visits RI this is a must visit. Top picture: Thai tamaring Salad Bottom: Dinner special grilled tofu with quinoa, greens, beans and Orange Sauce.  Music a bit edgy.. service is never fast because of the prep time, but always well worth the wait.
I'm not a vegetarian or vegan but some in my family are so we went for mothers day. I was very surprised how flavorful and satisfying their menu items were. A good time was had by all.
Amazing! Hubby had the Pastrami Reuben and I had the Special Grilled Cheese which had avocado, figs and spinach with cheddar cheese, Ridiculously Good! We'll be back👍

My daughter took me here while I was visiting her in Providence. I'm not vegetarian or vegan, but I love eating at vegan restaurants while traveling because it's a good way to eat healthy. I ordered the vegan Reuben and I swear it was so good I'd probably choose it again over real pastrami and melted cheese. This thing was awesome! Can't wait to visit Providence again to come back here!
Very spirited veggie burger -- by FAR the best I've ever had. It even looks like a rare real meat offering.
This place was so good, I plan to go back again later today for dinner. Excellent vegetarian and vegan options but don't let that stop any of you omnivores from coming. The food and staff are great!
Went once. Underwhelming. I am not into Vegan food so take that with a grain of salt. Might as well go to Rasoi next door where they have just as many Vegan options with more flavor.
Love this place
I love Garden Grille! Food is amazing. Staff is great!
Food is very good.
Absolutely love the Vegan food here!
This is a great place for vegetarians. Loved the cauliflower pattirs and the risotto.
Absolutely delicious! The Kidney Bean & Portabella Burger is divine
Veg restaurant lots of vegan gluten free and raw options. Didn't like the tostadas or portabella tacos but the nachos, blt, and burgers are good.
The tofu bacon and nachos are to die for
Delicious food. Great service.
AWESOME vegetarian and vegan food.  So great to go to a restaurant where I can eat anything on the menu.  My go to items are the amazing nachos and the Seitan Pastrami Reuben!

I've been here or ordered from here several times now. I'm not a vegetarian, but every time I've loved the food from here. the burger, the burrito, the salads, the quesadilla... all delicious... oh and the staff is really friendly, too.
The nachos are amazing and the vegan gluten free macaroni and cheese was really nice. If this was closer to me I would eat here all the time. Need more places like this everywhere.
I'm not a vegetarian or vegan actually I eat Keto and I found this restaurant to be very good. The prices more reasonable.
they have a lot of vegan options. I love tis place will definitely come here again. great service and clean and fun environment
Great food, service and atmosphere

Very good vegetarian food and decent value. Expect a 30-40 minute wait on a Saturday night. You can take a buzzer and go to any of the nearby cafes or restaurants while you wait. I ordered the portabella and kidney bean burger, which was delicious. My friend had the squash quesadilla, which she loved. We sat at the bar, and the service was good.
I Love this restaurant, have to wait awhile to be seated, but so worth it. Visit Wildflower for a coffee and conversation while you wait for a table.

It's the best vegetarian/vegan restaurant I've ever been to. Mind you, I'm not vegetarian or vegan but I seriously crave this place weekly. The Reuben is mind-blowing and the nachos hit the spot every time.
Wonderful food and ambience. The servers are very polite. I am yet to eat a meal here that I didn't like. This place is a vegan's delight.
Great Food!

Vegetarian Restaurants can be hit or miss...Sometimes they feel so sterile in their striving to be so pure, but Garden Grille is the exception. It's so wonderful to find this sweet little space that has so many great vegan choices. Reubans and tacos with excellent garnishes and a cute little cozy ambiance made this a delightful experience. I really enjoyed the feeling inside of this place and the service was very wonderful.
worst steakhouse ever!
Great food and attentive wait staff
Incredible vegan options
The best

So delicious! Specials are almost always exciting, main menu is so good. I have to have the korean tacos for an appetizer for the table it's too hard to go without having one. They have a full bar. The new renovation is really good and functional. Soothing atmosphere.
The tofu BLT is to die for! I recomend 100%! Prices are decent.
Had tacos they were good but pricey at just under $10 for 2
Can't stop thinking about the wonderful meal I had three days ago from the Garden Grille. 😁
Always good
Fantastic, as always.
Wonderful! The chief Great! All staff very nice!
I love their food. Excellent vegan and vegetarian foods served in a fun environment by friendly and helpful staff. The vegan Reuben is outrageous! I've never had anything I didn't like here.
Delicious. Every. Time.
love this place!!!

I'm not vegetarian, I will never be vegetarian, and when I hear vegetarian restaurant I usually dont get excited. From now on, though, I will get excited for garden grill. Friendly staff, good food, and reasonable prices.

Have I told you this place has my favorite vegan Reuben sandwich? The noise level used to be intolerable so I'd avoid going when super busy. They've now remodeled the place with acoustic ceiling tiles that really help cut down the jarring noise. Pleasant waitstaff. Now has a better bathroom too. :-) Unfortunately, there was a hair in my sandwich.
Great vegan food dishes. Even my meat eating friends enjoyed the delightful vegan food.
Good and healthy food, Love it.☺
Excellent vegetarian food ! The BLT and Ruben sandwiches are the best. Two thumbs up ! 👍👍
Great restaurant, been there many times.
Vegetarian heaven Absolutely delightful burger.
Great food options, although I wish there were more. Their food is vegetarian (*all can be made vegan) with great drinks available as well.
Very good place

The Garden Grill is still one of the best vegan/vegetarian restaurants in the Providence/Pawtucket area.  Their Butternut Squash Quesadillas and Lentil Tostadas are excellent.  If you enjoy vegetarian and vegan entrees I highly recommend it.
Great veggie place. Healthy. Casual. Comfort food. Inexpensive. Has bar as well.

Great food! But service is bad, and two times they have given me the non-vegan version of something when I asked for the vegan version and I’ve eaten it. Since my stomach is used to no dairy, it hurts my stomach and makes me breakout. Both times they didn’t seem to care, just made me wait even longer for a new one and didn’t discount it.
Interesting food
Friendly and attentive service with great food selections. First time and I went by myself but I didn't even feel awkward or anything.
Great food and friendly service

Cute spot, tons of incredible options, great, fast service! Their quesadilla is awesome but their seitan Reuben is probably the best vegan Reuben I’ve ever had! Their vegan cheeses are super melty and extremely realistic
The food is always amazing. Nice and clean and great atmosphere!

In the realm of vegetarian restaurants, Garden Grille is one of the best. Simple comfort foods and healthy choices done right.  The Korean tempeh tacos are amazing (though very sweet), the BLT is served on high quality bread with a perfect …

I love this place. It is so incredibly cute in here. It's cozy but also feels modern. I love the lights above the bar.  They always seem to be supporting some sort of non-profit charity, animal cause, or environmental issue (only giving plastic straws upon request, etc.) which should warm the hearts of anyone eating there.  Dishes I've gotten here/stole a bite of so far: Soup of the day (vegetable), sweet potato wedges, GF vegan mac & cheese, roasted butternut squash quesadilla, pastrami seitan reuben, and the classic veggie burger. I have LOVED every single one of these. My ONLY complaint was the mac & cheese desperately needed salt.  The waitstaff is always super attentive even with a constantly full dining room.  And since the dining room is usually full, there is sometimes a short wait. It's never been more than 10-15 minutes for me.
I had the stir-fry bowl and it was delicious! The staff was super friendly.

Absolute Amazing vegetarian food. I had the vegetarian BLT and the smoked tofu bacon was wonderful. I am also a huge fan of the Brussels Sprouts. I doubt there is anything on the menu that isn’t delicious.
Quite surprised with the selection of vegan choices. Had their ruben sandwich and was very satisfied. Serive was very good. I would recommend this place to anyone.

I love this place, everyone is always super nice. My fave is the BLT, never disappoints! Our other regular order everytime we visit is the BBQ Seitan; In the past it  has been phenomenal, unfortunately they changed the Seitan and I wish …
My favourite resturant..quality of their food is impeccable especially living a plant base diet.
The most incredible reuben ive had in my life.  Everything was perfection.  I assure you there is a bathroom in the back judt keep walking.
Great to have such a dependable high quality vegetarian restaurant in our neighborhood.
Delicious pizza and quesadilla. Nice outdoor place to sit and prompt service.
Delicious food and pretty good prices. The staff is very friendly, and the restaurant always seems busy. Pretty casual feel, which we like. The vegan BLT is incredible!

First time here and everything was phenomenal! The ambiance, the service, and ESPECIALLY the food. My boyfriend turned vegan about 2 months ago and this was one of the best options for him besides cooking at home. We will definitely be back for more!
One of my favorite restaurants on the east coast
Great food
Great place with good food, priced fair
Best casadilias around

I've heard great things about this place and all the rumors are true, it's amazing. The staff is extremely friendly. The decor is consistent with a modern vegan/raw restaurant. The food is incredible. A little more pricey than what one may expect, however, it is amazing and worth it. I had a simple salad with add-ons. It was the best salad I have had in months. Their homemade dressing delivers new flavor combinations that I have never experienced. I will definitely be back, next time I'm bringing my friends too!

Good food, great cocktails, unnecessary wait-time  When it comes to vegan/vegetarian food, Garden Grille does a good job with a slightly more diverse menu than its counterpart, The Grange. The cocktails are as delicious and innovative including my favorite one involving whiskey with cardamom bitters. The wait, however, is simply not worth it at this place. They funnel people into their “organic”-chic coffee shop two doors down, Wildflour (which, ironically doesn’t even have recycling!) prior to seating, even when the restaurant seemed to be empty. In our case, we had to wait an hour and five minutes. The ensuing dining experience (and cost) quite simply did not warrant such a wait.

I love this restaurant,  I hate the location.  I wish they would move to a bigger place.  I dislike Pawtucket, I'm sorry for being so blunt,  but it would be awesome if they would move this place to a different town.  Anyway...... Food is always awesome, people here are great.  I think this was the first Vegetarian restaurant I had gone to.  Many, many, years later I still love the place.  Food and drinks are excellent.  It's usually pretty busy and there isn't much seating.  I haven't been in a bit, but from what I understand now you get free coffee at the vegan bakery next door if you have to wait for a table.  That's cool.
Service was great, atmosphere was awesome, some great tunes playing in the background. Food to us was phenomenal. Will definitely come again.

We went on a Friday early afternoon (11am). It was not too busy when we arrived, but quickly filled up. The place is pretty small and has a trendy kind of vibe about it. The menu doesn't overwhelm you with a ton of choices (a good thing in my opinion), but is extensive enough where just about anyone can find something they would like. We had an appetizer which was delicious and perfectly portioned for two. For lunch we each tried the tofu BLT with avocado which was also ridiculously good. Our bill came to 35 dollars and some change which we both felt was more than reasonable for the portions and quality of food. We also both felt the wait staff were friendly, knowledgeable, and attentive which made the experience even better. I would highly recommend giving this place a visit!

Great food and nice atmosphere. The staff are friendly (though busy) and the restaurant has a real commitment to serving the community. Garden Grille is also Kosher (bonus) and Vegetarian (it has a number of Vegan items) and it is kid friendly.
Love those Nachos and we love one of the Chefs Chris V
First time trying this spot, I got the stir fry bowl & it was delicious. I’m most definitely coming back

I love this place!! I drive 28 miles to get here and it's well worth it. They do vegetarian cuisine up with a great presentation and make it fun, delicious, nutritious!! 5 Stars for food, decor and service!!
AMAZING. Awesome atmosphere, polite servers and a chef that goes above and beyond. The chef catered to my soy allergy so well and made a special dish that was spectacular.
Delish!

If you are ever in Providence, RI, you need to have a meal at, Garden Grille. I have NEVER had a  vegan/vegetarian meal that was good as the one I had last night. Absolutely incredible and the only way that their dishes can be prepared is with......sorcery. Next door is the Wildflower Bakery (owned by the same people.). I had a vegan chocolate chip cookie that was the best chocolate chip cookie I have EVER had. "This is not possible", I thought after one bite. An incredible experience!

I come here a lot, the food is amazing and almost anything can be made vegan (maybe everything? I haven't been told "no" yet). In a great spot right next to a vegan bakery too, so if you have to wait you can hang out there.
Decently satisfying vegetarian food at Chicago prices ($9-13). Played pretty hip indie music (MGMT, Vampire Weekend, Spoon). Hipsters galore.

So hard to find a good vegetarian restaurant.  This one nailed it! Veggie burger was one of the best I've had - Corn, green beans,  red peppers and more.  Service was super friendly.  Butternut black bean quesadilla was good too. Definitely coming back.
Always delicious and excellent service

We visited for the first time on a Friday night around 7:30 and were told there was a 30 minute wait for 2. We headed over to the Wild Flower, owned by the same people and were offered free coffee but got juice and a pasty instead. It felt like less than a 30 minute wait but I didn't actually time it. Once seated, food took longer than I would have liked to come out (I was starving before we even left home to go there) but it wasn't longer than I'd wait anywhere else. I got the butternut squash quesadilla and my husband got the saitan rueben minus the cheese. He was amazed at how "real" it tasted, meaning like an actual rueben. We both had enough food to take home left overs (love that). Our waitress and bartender were both super nice, friendly, down to earth. We were offered and accepted dessert on the house, Pumpkin Cheesecake. I'm eating it now and it's creamy but much lighter than typical cheesecake. I dig it. Last thing I can think of to comment on is the atmosphere. It was cute, cozy, had cool lighting decorations, but poor barstools... not very sturdy and not much room for my legs under the bar.  What else is there to say? We plan on going back for sure and glad to have found a place that's been around for 30+ years and off our radar all the while.
The vegan food is fresh and delicious!!! love the staff and atmosphere.
Wonderful vegan options. Loved the vegan tamales and burger! Service was wonderful!

We have been making the trip from Southeastern Connecticut for 2 years and always have wonderful meals. Checking out the menu today I feared some of our old favorites have been replaced, but not to worry. They added new items that are delicious and kept the old.
Great atmosphere, friendly staff, amazing food at a good price. Left very satisfied. Definitely a great place to bring picky omnivores.
Oh my God. This place is amazing! Reuben was really really delicious!
Always hit this spot on the way back from the Cape to Providence. The BEST!!!!

great food, experience and atmosphere! Wish I had gone long ago!  Gluten free and vegan foods that I can eat! I also avoid corn and soy. This has not been a issue. Besides I just found out the cook was someone I have known for years! And I would like to add b/c of people comments about the staff.. they are all professional. Some of them do not naturally smile like Barbie and Ken, but they are wonderful, caring, happy people if you take the time to talk to them. It is ALWAYS busy there..and things get full fast. Three stars because the food is well prepared and served and the space is nice.  However, it is nothing special and unbelievably overpriced.  As an example, I ordered a portobello wrap that came with a side of red cabbage slaw.  What I got was a wrap with three incredibly small sliced of portobello mushroom, barely noticeable, and loaded with the same red cabbage slaw that was already heaped on the plate.  If I had wanted a whole head of red cabbage I would have gone the Whole Foods, gotten an organic one, grated it myself and spent less than a 12th of what I paid for a plate of red cabbage.  I also had some soup, which was very good, but again highly priced and in this case a small portion as well.  I think it gets decent reviews because there isn't any competition.

I have been extremely happy almost every time I've gone. Excellent food, lots of fresh things. They do have some cheese items, but can substitute vegan cheese very easily.  They have lots and lots of business, so they do sometimes turn people away. For example, they don't usually make reservations for parties of less than six people.  Service is good, if occasionally slow on a busy night (what do you expect?). Friendly and super helpful.  EDIT July 27, 2009: With the downturned economy, the Garden Grille is often considerably less busy, so I've sometimes risked it even on a Saturday night.  Awesome food, excellent prices and services, would totally recommend it to vegan, vegetarian, or carnivore (no meat, but every carnivore I've brought has found something they like).  Be sure to ask how big the plate is.  Some of their appetizers and entrees are somewhat small (to me), while others are HUGE.  For example, if you order a plate of nachos as an appetizer, it's practically an entire meal all by itself.
